WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.233
See how you can make dynamic groups on Knox Manage

2
00:00:03.233 --> 00:00:08.766
which automatically adds users to groups based on predefined conditions!

3
00:00:09.833 --> 00:00:14.199
On the Knox Manage groups page, click "Create group" to start building a new group.

4
00:00:14.200 --> 00:00:15.533


5
00:00:15.533 --> 00:00:20.466
On the group creation page, set the group name and choose if this will be a user or device group

6
00:00:21.333 --> 00:00:21.366


7
00:00:21.366 --> 00:00:27.399
Here, select Dynamic membership so members are added automatically based on rules.

8
00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:28.533


9
00:00:28.533 --> 00:00:35.299
The Dynamic Group builder lets you add rule-based conditions, and set actions for when users join or leave.

10
00:00:35.300 --> 00:00:36.366


11
00:00:36.366 --> 00:00:42.566
For example, you can set your condition to add users to your group if their User ID contains a certain pattern.

12
00:00:42.566 --> 00:00:43.132


13
00:00:43.133 --> 00:00:43.366


14
00:00:43.366 --> 00:00:50.199
If you set multiple conditions, you can choose if a user must meet all of them or just one of them to be automatically added to the group.

15
00:00:52.466 --> 00:00:58.499
Then, you can click "Preview group members" to see which users will be added to your group based on your conditions.

16
00:01:00.666 --> 00:01:04.099
With the condition set, you can enable the option to automatically

17
00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:08.733
push the group's assigned profiles and apps whenever a new user is added.

18
00:01:08.733 --> 00:01:13.199
This ensures that new members instantly receive required resources.

19
00:01:15.533 --> 00:01:19.666
Click 'CREATE' to finalize and activate the dynamic group.

20
00:01:19.666 --> 00:01:20.732


21
00:01:20.733 --> 00:01:28.466
Your dynamic user group is now live, automatically adding any user whose department matches your rules

22
00:01:28.466 --> 00:01:30.899
while also applying assigned profiles and apps.

23
00:01:31.533 --> 00:01:38.266
To learn more about Knox Manage dynamic groups, please see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com.

24
00:01:38.266 --> 00:01:39.299
Thanks for watching!
